article.description: Cameron Johnson and Jarrell Brantley made four straight free throws in the final seconds to secure victory as College of Charleston thwarted a late Towson rally for a 62-57 win on Thursday night.
article.headline: College of Charleston holds off Towson for 62-57 win
article.linkText: College of Charleston holds off Towson for 62-57 win
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Cameron Johnson and Jarrell Brantley made four straight free throws in the final seconds to secure victory as College of Charleston thwarted a late Towson rally for a 62-57 win on Thursday night. Towson led 30-27 at the break but Charleston charged back to take the lead for good following a Brantley jumper at the 11:05 mark. That started a 12-6 run for the Cougars who were up 58-53 with 56 seconds left. Towson's Eddie Keith II followed his own miss with a tip-in to close to 58-57 with 23 seconds remaining. Johnson and Brantley then hit the free throws to seal the win. Joe Chealey led Charleston (12-4, 3-0 CAA) with 22 points. Brantley added 19 points and grabbed 13 rebounds for the Cougars who have won four consecutive games. Arnaud William Adala Moto had 15 points for Towson (8-8, 0-3). Keith added seven points while grabbing 10 boards.
